('informatics', 'OOP', 'What is encapsulation in OOP?', '["Inheriting from a parent class", "Hiding internal state and requiring interaction through methods", "Creating multiple instances", "Overloading methods"]', 1, 'Encapsulation bundles data and methods while restricting direct access to internal state.'),
('informatics', 'OOP', 'What is inheritance in OOP?', '["Copying code manually", "A class acquiring properties of another class", "Deleting unused objects", "Encrypting data"]', 1, 'Inheritance allows a child class to inherit attributes and methods from a parent class.'),
